                                <condition>
                                    <p>
                                        Some natural fissures with a rough patch at the bottom, which potentially obscures part of the stem-line, and a protrubance at the top on the rock face. (Forstyh 1996, 97-100)
                                    </p>
                                </condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>
                                    <p>
                                        The inscription is about <depth unit="m">11</depth> from the entrance of the cave.<q>'From the photograph, approximately <height unit="cm">29</height> of stem-line is visible'</q> (Forsyth 1996, 97).The inscription has a near-vertical stem-line.
                                    </p>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>
                                <rs type="execution" key="carved" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/168.html">carved</rs>
                                <p>
                                        Strokes and letters are widely spaced and vary in length.<q>'The strokes appear V-shaped in section and are slashed across the surface of the rock. Some strokes, especially to the right of the stem, seem exceptionally long'</q> (Forsyth 1996, 97).
                                </p>
                                <height>Varies, with longer strokes to the right</height>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
